1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,056
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

2
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:18,393
Terrace House is a show about
six strangers living together,

3
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:20,270
and we observe how they interact.

4
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:23,523
All that we've prepared is
a beautiful home and automobiles.

5
00:00:23,607 --> 00:00:25,442
There is no script at all.

6
00:00:25,526 --> 00:00:28,612
The time has finally come.

7
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,907
After what happened last episode...

8
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:34,117
-What happened?
-Last time...

9
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:38,539
-Yusuke said he's thinking of leaving.
-That's right.

10
00:00:38,622 --> 00:00:40,290
Wasn't that what happened?

11
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:42,459
-He only told Naomi.
-Right.

12
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:43,543
-Yes.
-That's right.

13
00:00:43,627 --> 00:00:46,797
-Yes, it was a double shock.
-The other members don't know yet.

14
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,925
-Only Naomi knows right now.
-That's right.

15
00:00:50,008 --> 00:00:51,176
Wait a second!

16
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:56,514
Who are you?

17
00:00:56,599 --> 00:00:58,100
Excuse me. I'm Saito.

18
00:00:59,810 --> 00:01:02,229
-I didn't recognize you!
-Saito!

19
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:04,982
-I've got this on today.
-That hides 90% of you.

20
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,191
TSUKASA SAITO
TRENDY ANGEL

21
00:01:06,274 --> 00:01:07,735
90%? Only one tenth.

22
00:01:07,818 --> 00:01:12,405
-Why are you here today?
-I really love Terrace House.

23
00:01:12,489 --> 00:01:16,118
So I used my popularity,
told people how much I love it,

24
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:17,327
and then I was invited.

25
00:01:17,410 --> 00:01:21,665
-Yay!
-I'm honored. I'm honestly very nervous.

26
00:01:21,749 --> 00:01:24,459
Recently, I worked with Takeshi Kitano
and Ken Shimura,

27
00:01:24,542 --> 00:01:26,378
but this is even more nerve-wracking.

28
00:01:27,004 --> 00:01:29,673
You're making them feel bad.

29
00:01:29,757 --> 00:01:32,926
I feel like I can't disturb this scene.

30
00:01:33,010 --> 00:01:36,013
It's like getting my picture taken
at Disneyland.

31
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:37,723
It's at that level.

32
00:01:37,806 --> 00:01:40,058
Have you been a fan since the beginning?

33
00:01:40,142 --> 00:01:41,518
Yes, I have.

34
00:01:42,435 --> 00:01:46,481
Do you have any favorite people or scenes?

35
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:48,566
Well, to be honest...

36
00:01:48,651 --> 00:01:54,531
I've been asked in interviews
whether I've ever cried before.

37
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:59,703
The scene when Hansan is about to leave...

38
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:02,414
That's the most I've cried in my life.

39
00:02:02,998 --> 00:02:04,332
-You're kidding!
-Your entire life?

40
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:06,168
-You too, right?
-Me too!

41
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,252
These two cried, too.

42
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:09,046
-You're right!
-Yes, it's true.

43
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:12,800
I wondered why the rest of you
weren't crying.

44
00:02:12,883 --> 00:02:14,259
It was touching, right?

45
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:16,970
That was the most moved you felt
in your entire life?

46
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:18,681
-No way.
-It's the truth.

47
00:02:18,764 --> 00:02:21,850
I downloaded that scene and have it saved.

48
00:02:21,934 --> 00:02:24,102
-It's on your phone?
-So I can watch it any time.

49
00:02:24,186 --> 00:02:26,897
-No way!
-You understand the greatness of Hansan.

50
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,482
For us, it's like, why did he come?

51
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:32,444
-It was so great, wasn't it?
-It was.

52
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:34,154
How about this season?

53
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:36,740
I love Lauren.

54
00:02:36,824 --> 00:02:38,325
Really? You like Lauren?

55
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:40,661
I thought I wouldn't
since she seems so perfect,

56
00:02:40,744 --> 00:02:44,039
but she's been showing
some vulnerability lately.

57
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,540
Her true self, you mean.

58
00:02:45,623 --> 00:02:48,168
Yes. Well, that's a bad choice of words.

59
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:50,253
-Watch out for him. Careful.
-Yes.

60
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:55,968
Because of that,
she's slipped into my zone.

61
00:02:56,051 --> 00:02:58,428
-She was on a pedestal...
-That's exactly right.

62
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:01,473
-...but became human.
-I feel like I might have a chance.

63
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:05,435
-She's been stressed out lately.
-That's right.

64
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,187
Sparks flew last time.

65
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:10,983
-Because Lauren...
-Oh, Thanksgiving.

66
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:14,820
I know you want to spend time
with your family.

67
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:18,824
We can have our dinner earlier.

68
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:22,285
I might get in trouble, but okay.
That can't be helped.

69
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:25,705
Then don't tell us you'll be in trouble.

70
00:03:36,674 --> 00:03:41,054
Many people felt that she should've
just changed her schedule to begin with.

71
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:44,224
That's not true at all.

72
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:47,895
And then for her to say she's stressed.
Is that our fault?

73
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,731
And Naomi's farewell trip...

74
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:52,775
-They went snorkeling.
-That was nice.

75
00:03:52,858 --> 00:03:55,068
Avian's bottom was very attractive.

76
00:03:55,152 --> 00:03:57,946
-She does have a nice bottom.
-She does.

77
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:03,701
And between Yuya and Avian...

78
00:04:03,786 --> 00:04:06,538
things have been going well.

79
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:08,331
Are your feet ticklish?

80
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:12,252
Stop that! Seriously.

81
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:14,129
I'm sleepy.

82
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:16,882
-On the sofa outside.
-That's right.

83
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:20,469
-They should've kissed.
-Yes.

84
00:04:20,552 --> 00:04:23,597
-But he didn't make a move.
-He didn't.

85
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:26,724
And Yusuke will also be leaving
Terrace House...

86
00:04:26,809 --> 00:04:30,353
-Only Naomi knows.
-He only told Naomi.

87
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:33,023
You're leaving
Terrace House tomorrow, right?

88
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:36,276
I'm thinking of leaving soon, too.

89
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:38,862
-Shall we watch, Saito?
-It's gonna start.

90
00:04:38,946 --> 00:04:40,613
Thank you. Finally!

91
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,335
Naomi, I have to go.

92
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:55,212
Okay, I'll see you out.

93
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,256
The last time.

94
00:05:03,595 --> 00:05:05,638
-Good luck.
-Yeah.

95
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:08,976
-Sorry I can't see you off.
-That's all right.

96
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:15,190
-Here.
-Good luck in Japan.

97
