LAUREN TSAI, 18 YEARS OLD
ASPIRING ILLUSTRATOR, MODEL

148
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:15,180
YUYA SHIBUSAWA, 18 YEARS OLD
ASPIRING ACTOR

149
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:18,308
AVIAN KU, 26 YEARS OLD
SALESCLERK

150
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:21,436
ERIC DE MENDONCA, 27 YEARS OLD
CARPENTER

151
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:24,522
NAOMI LORRAINE FRANK, 23 YEARS OLD
UNDECIDED

152
00:09:24,606 --> 00:09:27,984
YUSUKE AIZAWA, 18 YEARS OLD
MUSICIAN, UKULELE PLAYER

153
00:09:38,995 --> 00:09:41,914
IZAKAYA TAKONOKI

154
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:44,917
-You're really leaving?
-Yeah.

155
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,504
I don't want you to. Really?

156
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,593
It's good timing.

157
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:55,512
I want to open the main café, too.

158
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:58,390
I want to focus on that more.

159
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:01,268
-Let's eat!
-Let's eat, let's eat.

160
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:06,148
When I'm with you, it's like I'm 18 again.

161
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:10,402
It's both good and bad.

162
00:10:11,528 --> 00:10:12,779
Yeah.

163
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:16,449
I have the most fun hanging out with you.

164
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,286
We're probably similar.

165
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:21,996
Yeah.

166
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:24,624
You know how...

167
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:29,671
I said I was interested in Lauren?

168
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,881
The age difference is significant...

169
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,926
and we work together.

170
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:40,515
So I don't want things to get complicated.

171
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:44,811
And Yusuke went out on a date with her.

172
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:47,647
I think it was better...

173
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:50,775
that he went out with her rather than me.

174
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:57,073
What are you going to do
if the new girl is really cute?

175
00:10:57,157 --> 00:11:02,036
Well, I really like Avian right now...

176
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:04,497
so I don't think it would matter.

177
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,041
Nice.

178
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:09,836
She's probably the least pretty
of the three.

179
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:13,923
But after talking with her
and getting to know her...

180
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:16,259
she's really pretty to me.

181
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:19,262
She's like an older sister,

182
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:22,056
but she can still put herself in my shoes.

183
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:24,767
And sometimes she'll teach me things.

184
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:29,522
-She affects me in different ways.
-That's good.

185
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:33,150
I'm glad we did this.
It's been a while.

186
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:37,029
-Let's still meet up even after you leave.
-Yeah, let's.

187
00:11:46,789 --> 00:11:49,292
LOUKIE WONG
AVIAN'S MOTHER

188
00:11:54,964 --> 00:12:00,470
HENRY CHAN
MERCHANDISING DIRECTOR

189
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:26,955
Hey.

190
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:32,084
How are you?

191
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:35,212
We said we'd come see the sunset,
but it's totally dark.

192
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:37,715
It's totally night time now.

193
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:41,886
This is nice, too.
There are even Christmas decorations.

194
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:43,930
-Bon appétit.
-Bon appétit.

195
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,601
It's delicious.

196
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:52,021
You look different today.

197
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:54,065
Is that a compliment? Thanks.

198
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,694
-Is that a compliment?
-No, it's not.

199
00:13:02,949 --> 00:13:03,950
This is really good.

200
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:08,705
You seem happy.

201
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:12,375
The food is good,
and I'm having dinner with you.

202
00:13:15,462 --> 00:13:18,005
-Yeah.
-How was the talk?

203
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:20,758
-Good?
-It was.

204
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:24,596
-We talked about starting a bikini line.
-You did?

205
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,558
What did your mom say?
Was she surprised?

206
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:30,059
She agreed with me.

207
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:31,811
Would the brand...

208
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:34,981
be part of 88 Tees?

209
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:37,900
No, it'll be my own thing.

210
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:41,070
-I'll come up with a name.
-I see.

211
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:45,867
People always ask if I'm taking over.

212
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:48,285
When they do, it makes me feel...

213
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,746
-You don't like it?
-No.

214
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:53,583
I feel the pressure.
So I can't picture it now, but...

215
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:56,293
-But?
-When the time is right.

216
00:13:56,378 --> 00:14:00,214
You're working at your mom's store...

217
00:14:00,297 --> 00:14:02,174
but you have your way
of doing things, too.

218
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:07,263
So you should work on developing that.

219
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:10,808
Even if the bikini line fails...

220
00:14:10,892 --> 00:14:13,144
I think you'd succeed with anything.

221
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:15,397
Of course,
succeeding with the bikini line is best.

222
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:17,440
Yeah.

223
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:21,778
-I'll be rooting for you.
-Thanks.

224
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:25,615
You're an active guy.

225
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,909
We're alike in that way.

226
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,788
We are.

227
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:33,706
It's partially why I was attracted to you.

228
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:36,584
Really? Because I'm active?

229
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:40,880
-Active people--
-I like girls I can work out with.

230
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:43,090
